comment: Conway's Simplicity Theorem. Given ` A ` preceeding ` B ` , there is a unique surreal of minimal length separating them. This is a fundamental property of surreals and will be used (via surreal cuts) to prove many properties later on. (Contributed by Scott Fenton, 8-Dec-2021.)
